cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the generalization and excess risk bounds for neural nets, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of entropy measures and the Gibbs posterior distribution also suggests a connection to information theory and statistical inference. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the use of multilevel structures and algorithms suggests a connection to neural engineering (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SI).
